<HEADLINE>
<P>
QUAKE AID / A RESOURCE GUIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 LOANS 
</P>
<P>
 A loan fund has been established to help owners repair or strengthen 
earthquake-damaged historic buildings. 
</P>
<P>
 Owners of historic properties can use the loans to stabilize, weatherize or 
make emergency repairs to residential, religious and commercial buildings. 
</P>
<P>
 Loans up to $20,000 are available at 4% interest. There is a $100 application 
fee. The program is sponsored by the National Trust for Historic Preservation, 
First Interstate Bank of California and the Getty Conservation Institute. 
Information: (213) 614-2206. 
</P>
<P>
 SHELTER 
</P>
<P>
 The American Red Cross continues to aid Santa Monica area residents affected 
by the quake. 
</P>
<P>
 A service center at 1527 4th St. is open from 9 a.m. to 7 p.m. daily. The 
Santa Monica chapter provides food, shelter, health care, counseling and other 
services. Information: (310) 260-9187. 
</P>
<P>
 COUNSELING 
</P>
<P>
 Airport Marina Counseling Service offers free earthquake discussion groups. 
</P>
<P>
 Drop-in groups meet daily. The center is at 6228 W. Manchester Ave., Los 
Angeles. Information: (310) 670-1410. 
</P>
