<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: LOS ANGELES; ELECTRIC SHUTTLE BUS SERVICE BEGINS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles International Airport will introduce today the first of four 
electric shuttle buses for the regular route between remote parking lots and 
the main terminal. 
</P>
<P>
 The battery-powered buses emit 97% less pollution than diesel-powered vehicles 
and carry 32 passengers, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Use of the one bus will eliminate more than 5,000 pounds of smog-forming 
emissions this year, Councilwoman Ruth Galanter said. Three more buses are 
scheduled to be added later in the year. 
</P>
