<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: PASADENA; GREEN TO SUPERVISE MUNICIPAL COURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pasadena Municipal Court Judge Terry Green was recently elected by fellow 
judges to serve as presiding judge this year. Green, 46, is responsible for 
assigning cases, overseeing court operations and working with county officials 
and the supervising judge of Pasadena Superior Court on a proposal to combine 
the staffs and tasks of both courts. 
</P>
<P>
 A graduate of USC Law Center, Green worked for 15 years as a Los Angeles 
County deputy district attorney and spent five years in business litigation 
before he was named to the Municipal Court in June, 1992 by Gov. Pete Wilson. 
</P>
