<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: POMONA; ACCOUNTING FIRM SELECTED TO AUDIT 2 CAL POLY OFFICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal Poly Pomona announced this week that the accounting firm Deloitte & Touche 
has been selected to conduct a comprehensive audit of two campus offices that 
have been embroiled in controversy the past year. 
</P>
<P>
 The move comes five months after the California State University chancellor's 
office recommended the review in a report that found numerous policy violations 
in actions related to Cal Poly's continuing education office and its 
educational foundation, which manages campus services such as the bookstores 
and cafeteria. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials said the audit has been delayed because of problems in obtaining a 
usable bid. The audit by the Wilton, Conn.-based firm is expected to take six 
weeks, but a Cal Poly spokeswoman said Tuesday she did not know how much the 
audit would cost or when it would begin. 
</P>
