<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: PASADENA; CALTECH TO CONTINUE MANAGEMENT OF JPL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Caltech has signed a five-year contract to manage the Jet Propulsion 
Laboratory, NASA's lead center for solar system exploration. 
</P>
<P>
 The contract includes roughly $1 billion annually for JPL operations. Also, 
Caltech receives a management fee of at least $6 million each year. The fee 
could increase to $18 million, depending on Caltech's performance review from 
NASA. 
</P>
<P>
 Caltech has managed the 7,300-employee laboratory since NASA's inception in 
1958. 
</P>
