<HEADLINE>
<P>
AROUND THE VALLEY . . .: POLICE BLOTTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 ALHAMBRA: A man shot in the face on Chinese New Year's Eve at the Jumbo 
Chinese Restaurant at 203 W. Valley Blvd. remained in critical condition at 
County-USC Medical Center but is improving, police said. Mingo Ho, 44, of 
Arcadia, was shot Feb. 9 as he tried to stop two robbers from taking money from 
the restaurant. 
</P>
<P>
 ANGELES NATIONAL FOREST: Sheriff's deputies and search-and-rescue crews found 
17-year-old Chris Steingart of Pasadena in the forest after a six-hour search 
Saturday. Steingart had gotten lost during a mountain bike ride. 
</P>
<P>
 BALDWIN PARK: A man who refused to give police his name was arrested on 
suspicion of drunk driving Sunday afternoon after he allegedly caused two 
accidents, injuring one person and damaging several cars. 
</P>
<P>
 IRWINDALE: Patrolman George Natzel recovered his own stolen car Sunday 
morning. As he stood with another officer during a routine traffic stop, Natzel 
watched his white 1981 Chevrolet Malibu cruise by and turn right on Alpha 
Street. Natzel hopped in his patrol car and stopped the vehicle just as it was 
pulling into an auto-wrecking shop. Two suspects were arrested and Natzel got 
his car back undamaged. 
</P>
<P>
 PASADENA: A car accident at Glen Avenue and Washington Boulevard killed one 
Pasadena resident and seriously injured another Sunday night, police said. 
Durrell Carr, 29, was killed when his car slammed into a light pole at high 
speed. His passenger, Darren Lockett, 26, was taken to Huntington Hospital in 
serious condition. 
</P>
<P>
 POMONA: Two Pomona men were shot and killed Friday about 3 a.m., police said. 
James F. Bailey Jr., 50, and Lamar Harris, 34, were standing near a pickup when 
an unidentified man drove up in a Cadillac and fired several shots. Bailey was 
shot in the chest and died on arrival at Pomona Valley Medical Center. Harris, 
who was wounded in the head, was pronounced dead. No arrests have been made. 
</P>
<P>
 POMONA: A 70-year-old Pomona man found shot to death in his home about noon 
Monday was murdered, police said. George Pickens' body was discovered in his 
house at 210 W. 8th St. after friends told officers they had not seen him since 
Friday. George Lincoln, 46, who lived with Pickens off and on, was arrested 
Monday and charged with murder. Lincoln later said the shooting was the result 
of an argument over the handgun, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 SOUTH PASADENA: Two men robbed a Bank of America branch in the 900 block of 
Fair Oaks Avenue on Thursday about 12:30 p.m. The two told a teller they had a 
weapon and then escaped with $582, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 WEST COVINA: A 17-year-old from West Covina was stabbed to death about 
midnight Sunday during a fight at a bachelor party on South Indian Summer 
Avenue, police said. Daryl Smith had argued with Brian Stinson, 20, of Laguna 
Hills over a tip for a stripper at the party. Their words eventually turned to 
blows and then Stinson allegedly stabbed Smith several times in the torso. 
Stinson and his girlfriend, 20-year-old Jennifer Biedrycki of Covina, have been 
charged with murder. Biedrycki allegedly kicked Smith several times during the 
fight.  
</P>
<P>
 WEST COVINA: A 15-year-old from Rowland Heights was shot in the head Sunday at 
12:30 a.m. after two cars filled with gang members began exchanging insults 
near Nogales Avenue and Shakespeare Drive, police said. Front-seat passenger 
Reynaldo Castillo Canlas was hit in the back of the head by gunfire and killed 
instantly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
