<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 BEVERLY HILLS: South Beverly Drive shoppers will get valet parking courtesy of 
the city until a city-owned parking structure damaged in the Jan. 17 earthquake 
is repaired. 
</P>
<P>
 The 240-space parking facility at 216 S. Beverly Drive will require about $1 
million in repairs, which may take up to five months to complete, City Manager 
Mark Scott said. 
</P>
<P>
 Losing that much parking for so long will have a "huge impact on businesses on 
South Beverly Drive," Scott said. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council on Tuesday approved a plan under which the city will pay 
about $5,000 per month for a valet company to park as many as 350 vehicles per 
day in the 200 blocks of El Camino and Reeves drives. The Chamber of Commerce 
and the Southwest Homeowners Assn. approved the plan. 
</P>
<P>
 The city plans to seek partial reimbursement of the costs from the Federal 
Emergency Management Agency, Scott said. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The city has agreed to pay $510,000 for a small parcel owned by the Beverly 
Hills Land Corp. 
</P>
<P>
 The 12,000-square-foot lot is on 3rd Street between Maple Drive and Foothill 
Road, City Manager Mark Scott said. 
</P>
<P>
 The city has been looking into acquiring additional land in the so-called 
industrial area near the Civic Center. 
</P>
<P>
 The purchase is contingent upon an environmental review of the property to 
verify there is no hazardous waste. The city already owns nine acres of 
developable land in the same area, intended for such municipal uses as a 
community center. 
</P>
<P>
 MEETINGS NEXT WEEK 
</P>
<P>
 * Beverly Hills: no meeting. (310) 285-2400. 
</P>
<P>
 * Culver City: no meeting. (310) 202-5851. 
</P>
<P>
 * Los Angeles: 10 a.m. Tuesday, Wednesday and Friday. 200 N. Spring St. (213) 
485-3126. 
</P>
<P>
 * Malibu: 6:30 p.m. Monday. Hughes Laboratory, 3011 Malibu Canyon Road. (310) 
456-2489. 
</P>
<P>
 * Santa Monica: 6:30 p.m. Tuesday. 1685 Main St. (310) 393-9975. 
</P>
<P>
 * West Hollywood: 7 p.m. Tuesday. West Hollywood Park Auditorium, 647 N. San 
Vicente Blvd. (310) 854-7460. 
</P>
