<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL NEWS: HAWTHORNE; SMOKING TO BE BANNED IN ALL CITY BUILDINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Smoke-filled rooms at Hawthorne City Hall will be a thing of the past after a 
smoking ban in all enclosed city buildings takes effect next month. 
</P>
<P>
 Council members voted 3-0 Monday night to approve the ban, which the city 
employees union backed with a petition drive. Council members Steve Andersen 
and Ginny Lambert were absent for the vote because of illness. 
</P>
<P>
 Not everyone was pleased with the new ordinance, however, including several 
staff members and residents, who took some of their few remaining indoor smoke 
breaks during recesses at Monday's meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
