<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL NEWS: EL SEGUNDO; COUNCIL CANDIDATES FORUM IS RESCHEDULED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An El Segundo candidates forum, postponed after the daughter of a city 
councilman was slain, has been rescheduled for Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The forum, sponsored by the El Segundo Taxpayers Assn., will be at 7 p.m. at 
Joslyn Center, 339 Sheldon St. 
</P>
<P>
 Six candidates, including Councilman Alan West, are competing for two council 
seats in the April 12 election. 
</P>
<P>
 Tairree Lynne West, 25, died after she was attacked in an apparent robbery 
Feb. 9. 
</P>
