<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL NEWS: ROLLING HILLS ESTATES; HEARING ON PROPOSED DAY-CARE CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A public hearing on a proposal to set up a day-care center on Wildhorse Lane 
in Rolling Hills Estates will be held at 7:30 p.m. Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The proposal, by Sheryl Yim, was approved by the city Planning Commission, but 
Councilwoman Jacki McGuire appealed the decision to the City Council after 
residents complained that a child-care center should not be in a residential 
neighborhood.  
</P>
<P>
 The hearing is in council chambers at Palos Verdes Drive North and Crenshaw 
Boulevard. SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
</TEXT>
