<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Italian journalists lost their credentials Wednesday for two days because 
they had carried a video camera into Tuesday's five-kilometer women's 
cross-country ski race. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lillehammer Olympic Organizing Committee said the credentials had been 
picked up because only rights-holders -- CBS, Eurosport and other organizations 
that paid to televise the Games -- were allowed to use video cams at the 
venues. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 From Hugin, the official newspaper of the Lillehammer Games: 
</P>
<P>
 "Fire stations in the Olympic region have received several false alarms in the 
last few days. The reason for this is that too many people in the region are 
taking showers with the door open and the steam activates the fire alarm. 
Johnny Haarberg, duty officer at Lillehammer's fire station, urges everybody 
taking a shower to shut the bathroom door to prevent steam reaching the 
alarms." MIKE KUPPER 
