<TEXT>
<P>
 Now, here's a cause you can get behind: Some U.S. mogul skiers wore gold 
armbands during the finals, protesting that freestyle ballet has not been made 
an Olympic sport. 
</P>
<P>
 "It is a shame that some of the world's best athletes are not able to compete 
in the Olympics," said Liz McIntyre, the silver-medal winner in moguls. 
</P>
<P>
 But McIntyre was not among the skiers wearing an armband. 
</P>
<P>
 "I didn't wear mine, frankly, because I forgot," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Add McIntyre: Her parents came to Lillehammer to watch her in the Olympics. 
McIntyre, who grew up in New Hampshire but now lives in Winter Park, Colo., 
said her mother loves Norway. 
</P>
<P>
 "My mother raises sheep," she said. "She weaves and knits. She's excited to be 
in Norway with all the wool and buttons." CHRIS DUFRESNE 
