<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; CHANEY ABSENT, DEFENSE THERE IN TEMPLE VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Though he scored 24 points in No. 13 Temple's 65-56 Atlantic 10 victory over 
St. Bonaventure on Wednesday night, Eddie Jones couldn't wait for the game to 
end. 
</P>
<P>
 He and his teammates are tired of hearing questions about Coach John Chaney, 
who missed the game at Olean, N.Y., while he served a one-game suspension 
imposed by the school after he charged Massachusetts Coach John Calipari after 
Temple's 56-55 loss Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 "We can't wait until this whole thing blows over," Jones said. "It'll be nice 
to have coach back." 
</P>
<P>
 Chaney is expected to return when Temple plays No. 5 Louisville on Sunday in 
Orlando, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
 In Chaney's absence, his trademark zone defense was the key to Temple's 
victory. "He's irreplaceable," assistant Jim Maloney said, "but there's a John 
Chaney stamp on this team that followed without him." 
</P>
<P>
 Temple (18-4, 11-3) beat the Bonnies (9-12, 3-8) for the 23rd time in a row. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 1 Arkansas 102, Alabama 81 -- Corliss Williamson scored 10 points in the 
first four minutes of the second half at Fayetteville, Ark., as the Razorbacks 
(19-2, 9-2) avenged a Southeastern Conference loss to Alabama (13-8, 8-4) that 
had knocked them from the No. 1 spot earlier in the season. 
</P>
<P>
 Oklahoma St. 63, No. 4 Kansas 59 -- Brooks Thompson forced overtime with a 
jump shot with 10 seconds to play, then sank two free throws with 10 seconds 
left in overtime to seal the upset victory for the Cowboys (17-7, 6-3 Big 
Eight) over Kansas (21-4, 6-3) in Stillwater, Okla. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 6 Duke 84, Virginia 54 -- Grant Hill and Antonio Lang scored 15 points 
each in the first half at Durham, N.C., for the Blue Devils (18-3, 9-3 Atlantic 
Coast). 
</P>
<P>
 No. 7 Michigan 89, Iowa 76 -- Juwan Howard scored 24 points at Ann Arbor, 
Mich., and the Wolverines (18-4, 10-2 Big Ten) won their seventh game in a row. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 9 Purdue 67, No. 24 Wisconsin 64 -- Glenn Robinson, the Division I scoring 
leader, had 27 points and 16 rebounds at West Lafayette, Ind., where the 
Boilermakers (21-3, 9-3 Big Ten) withstood a late three-point assault by 
Wisconsin (15-6, 6-6). 
</P>
<P>
 No. 12 Missouri 79, Iowa St. 72 -- Jevon Crudup scored eight of their 14 
points in overtime as the Tigers (19-2, 10-0 Big Eight) escaped with a victory 
at Iowa State. 
</P>
<P>
 Tulane 66, No. 21 Alabama-Birmingham 60 -- LeVeldro Simmons scored 16 points, 
including the clinching free throws with 39 seconds remaining, as the Green 
Wave (13-9) upset Alabama-Birmingham (18-5) at New Orleans. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 17 Florida 91, Georgia 79 -- Craig Brown and Dan Cross each scored 21 
points for the Gators (20-4, 10-2 SEC) in a victory over the Bulldogs (11-12, 
5-6) at Gainesville, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 23 Cincinnati 78, No. 18 Saint Louis 73 -- Curtis Bostic scored 11 of his 
15 points in the second half at Cincinnati where the Bearcats (17-7, 5-4 Great 
Midwest) beat the Billikens (19-3, 5-3). 
</P>
<P>
 No. 20 Minnesota 94, Penn St. 66 -- Voshon Lenard scored 30 points for the 
Gophers (18-7, 8-4 Big Ten) in a victory over Penn State (10-10, 3-8) at 
Minneapolis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
