<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIVISION I-AA GIRLS' BASKETBALL; YBARRA HELPS STOP ESPERANZA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gina Ybarra's strong defensive performance in the final two minutes of the 
game helped Fountain Valley to a 62-58 victory over Esperanza in a Southern 
Section Division I-AA wild-card game Wednesday at Fountain Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 After Erin Avila made a three-point shot to give the Barons a 57-56 lead with 
1 minute 41 seconds left in the game, Ybarra stole an Aztec pass, setting up a 
basket by Lisa Feng. 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza's Kimberly Hayashi made two free throws with 17 seconds left to cut 
the margin to one and Hayashi's quick foul put Jen Ludwicki on the free-throw 
line with 16 seconds remaining. She made the first free throw to give Fountain 
Valley a 60-58 lead. She missed the second, but Ybarra got the offensive 
rebound. 
</P>
<P>
 She was fouled and made both free throws to preserve the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 "Gina worked hard without the ball all game and the effort paid off in the 
end," Fountain Valley Coach Carol Strausburg said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Barons (17-9) advance to a first-round game at San Gabriel Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley got out to a 17-10 lead in the first quarter, but Esperanza 
bounced back to take the lead with five minutes left in the first half. The 
teams were tied at the half, 27-27. 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza (15-10) built a seven-point lead early in the fourth quarter before 
Fountain Valley rallied. 
</P>
<P>
 The Aztecs' second-half attack was led by Lindsay Foss, who scored nine points 
off six offensive rebounds, and Jodie Howard, who made three of her four 
three-pointers in the third quarter. Howard finished with 17 points and Foss 
and Kristy Kierulff each had 13. 
</P>
<P>
 Two baskets after offensive rebounds by Foss gave Esperanza its final lead of 
the game, 56-54. 
</P>
<P>
 Ludwicki scored 21 points, Nicole Strange had 14 and Feng had 11 for Fountain 
Valley. Strange scored eight in the final quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley stopped a three-game losing streak. 
</P>
</TEXT>
