<HEADLINE>
<P>
DRAMATIC GOLD EASILY WINS BRADBURY STAKES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL CHRISTINE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dramatic Gold, who was not an early nominee for the Triple Crown races, 
immediately went to the front Wednesday and had no trouble outfinishing the 
7-10 favorite Numerous for a two-length victory in the $80,700 Bradbury Stakes 
at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
 The Slew o' Gold-American Drama gelding, ridden by Corey Black for trainer 
David Hofmans and owners-breeders John and Betty Mabee, was timed in 1:48 2/5, 
four-fifths of a second slower than the stakes record. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Chris McCarron, who is Dehere's regular jockey, won't be available to ride the 
Kentucky Derby candidate in the Fountain of Youth Stakes on Saturday at 
Gulfstream Park. The Santa Anita stewards have suspended McCarron for five 
days, starting Saturday, for his ride on Hill Pass in Sunday's San Antonio 
Handicap. BILL CHRISTINE 
</P>
