<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; HERNANDEZ LEADS GOLDEN WEST VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Roseann Hernandez, who had two hits and two runs batted in, drove in Shelley 
Nelson in the bottom of the seventh inning to give Golden West a 4-3 
nonconference softball victory over San Diego Mesa Wednesday at Golden West. 
</P>
<P>
 Winning pitcher Vivian Alvarado (2-0) entered the game in the fifth inning and 
struck out seven of eight.Golden West is 2-2. San Diego Mesa is 2-4. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 12, Pasadena 1 -- Jennifer Allchin had four hits and scored two runs 
to lead Cypress (8-1). Jackie Ruiz, Kim Stiglbauer and Jenny Lopez combined for 
a two-hitter, with Ruiz picking up the victory. Cypress scored six of its runs 
on wild pitches. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference baseball: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast 13, Palomar 4 -- Brian Igoe's two-run homer in the first inning 
helped the host Pirates build a lead. They scored six runs in the first two 
innings. 
</P>
<P>
 Palomar (1-4) pitchers walked 11 and gave up 11 hits to Orange Coast (3-3). 
Freshman George Wise earned the victory in relief, pitching three scoreless 
innings. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference golf: 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 388, Los Angeles Mission 431, Cerritos 433 -- Cypress' Chris 
Castellano shot one-under-par 71 at Cypress Golf Club. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference men's tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 6, Santa Barbara 3 -- Tim Morstad and Jeremy Driscoll each won 
their singles matches, then teamed to win at No. 2 doubles, 6-2, 6-4, for 
visiting Saddleback (1-0). Billy Casas won in singles, 6-0, 6-0, for 
Saddleback. 
</P>
