<TEXT>
<P>
 BUFFER ZONE: After allowing a new high school to tap into Oxnard's water 
supply (B1), state planners signed off on an agreement to shield 4,575 acres of 
farmland from development. . . . But the approval kills a push to add another 
1,200 acres to the greenbelt between Ventura and Oxnard. . . . "I'm 
disappointed," said Jean Harris, who with other environmentalists asked that 
the greenbelt be expanded to include an agricultural strip surrounding the new 
Oxnard High School. "I just hope the land that was left out doesn't become 
vulnerable." 
</P>
<P>
 TOP DOG: Simi Valley Police Officer Sterling Johnson and his canine partner 
Charly took top honors over the weekend at the Bakersfield Canine Trials. The 
team beat out more than 50 competitors from across the state. . . . "It says 
more about the skills of the handler than it does about the dog," Lt. Tony 
Harper said. Charly follows in the footsteps of Atlas, a back-to-back world 
champion also handled by Johnson, a 12-year police veteran. 
</P>
<P>
 POSTER PRODUCE: California Strawberry Festival officials Wednesday unveiled 
the art that will grace posters and T-shirts promoting the annual event. For 
the second year in a row, San Ramon artist Penny Soto has designed the 
festival's official artwork: a silver bowl crowned with the berries. . . . 
Hidden within the piece are balloons, a clown's face and other items. "When 
people discover or rediscover something hidden in the shadows, it's a 
revelation that makes them feel good," Soto said. . . . The strawberry festival 
will be held May 21 and 22 at College Park near Oxnard College. 
</P>
<P>
 FAB FIVE: Bringing college basketball mania to a normally placid beach town, 
the Ventura College Pirates are one of the hottest tickets in town (Ventura 
Life, Page 24). . . . The men's basketball team is ranked No. 1 among 
California community colleges and is one of the top ones in the nation. . . . 
Beaten only twice in 31 games this season, it draws the largest crowds in the 
county for an indoor event. 
</P>
