COMMUNITY NEWS: WHITTIER; RIO HONDO COLLEGE PRESIDENT TO LEAVE POST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rio Hondo Community College President Alex Sanchez will leave in June to take 
the top post at the Albuquerque Technical and Vocational Institute in New 
Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
 Sanchez, who recently received a two-year contract extension, made the 
announcement at last week's college board meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 Sanchez has been president of the Whittier community college since 1989, and 
had been active on state accreditation panels. He headed the accreditation team 
that investigated troubled Compton Community College last year. 
</P>
<P>
 The board will meet later this month to choose an interim president 
</P>
