<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAKE FOREST; MISSING MAN WITH ALZHEIMER'S SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies are looking for a 75-year-old man suffering from 
Alzheimer's disease who failed to return home from a trip to a store Tuesday 
afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
 A Sheriff's Department spokesman said Ernest William Constable left his home 
on Ridge Route to go to a local hardware store and did not come back.Several 
hours later, his wife calledthe department to report him missing. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputies checked several businesses in the area but weren't able to locate 
Constable. 
</P>
<P>
 Constable is 5-foot-8 and weighs about 160 pounds. His eyes are blue and he 
was last seen wearing a long-sleeve plaid shirt, blue jeans and white tennis 
shoes. Constable was driving a white 1991 Ford Tempo with California license 
plate number 2VMM799. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputies said Constable suffers from short-term memory loss related to 
Alzheimer's, but is otherwise in good health. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with information about his whereabouts is asked to call the Sheriff's 
Department at (714) 647-7044 or (714) 647-1832. FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
