<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FIREFIGHTERS BURN BRUSH ON RANCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 County firefighters burned 850 acres of private grazing land in South County 
this week to try to prevent future brush fires, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The prescribed burn took place at Rancho Mission Viejo, a cattle ranch, 
between Ronald W. Caspers Regional Park and Camp Pendleton, Tuesday and 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Firefighters targeted patches of dead, dry brush to encourage the growth of 
young vegetation that is edible by wild animals, said Kathleen Cha, a 
spokeswoman with the Orange County Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about the prescribed burn, contact (714) 744-0492. 
</P>
</TEXT>
