<P>
ABDUCTED BOY SEEN WITH BIOLOGICAL PARENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 4-year-old boy taken last weekend from his foster home in Rancho Santa 
Margarita was sighted Wednesday with his biological parents in Anaheim, the 
Sheriff's Department reported. 
</P>
<P>
 An unidentified witness spotted Taj Yaser Jayyusi and the couple in a car 
going westbound on Orange Avenue from Beach Boulevard at 4:40 p.m., authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 When Taj disappeared Saturday morning, authorities said they feared that Yaser 
Majed Jayyusi, 55, a Jordanian national, and Deborah Ann Jayyusi, 35, might 
attempt to flee the country with the boy, who has been in foster care for two 
years. The couple also have a daughter in foster care in Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities would not reveal why the two children were removed from the 
Jayyusis' home. The Jayyusis are permitted weekly, court-monitored visits with 
the children. 
</P>
<P>
 Police believe the boy was taken from a garage that had been converted to a 
playroom, while his foster mother was taking a shower. The foster mother, Susan 
White, said the garage door was open about a foot. 
</P>
<P>
 White, 43, had started adoption proceedings, and a hearing to terminate the 
Jayyusis' parental rights was scheduled for Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with information regarding Taj is asked to call the Sheriff's 
Department at (714) 647-7000. 
</P>
<P>
 The Jayyusis were driving a yellow 1980 Oldsmobile Delta, according to Lt. Dan 
Martini. 
</P>
