<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA POLICE OFFICER HOSPITALIZED AFTER BEING SHOT; 3 MEN, YOUTH HELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 20-year-veteran of the Santa Ana Police Department was shot in the hand and 
arm Wednesday while responding to reports of shots being fired near El Salvador 
Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Police arrested four people, including a 15-year-old youth who surrendered a 
gun and who police believe fired the shots. 
</P>
<P>
 Lt. Robert Chavez, 45, was reported in good condition at Western Medical 
Center, where he was to undergo surgery to remove bone fragments, said Santa 
Ana Police Lt. Robert Helton. Helton said the shooting was the department's 
first in about six years. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's not a life-threatening injury," Helton said. "He's in good condition." 
</P>
<P>
 Of the four people held in the incident, Helton said, only the 15-year-old is 
expected to be charged. 
</P>
