<HEADLINE>
<P>
A GUIDE TO COPING WITH THE QUAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Times researchers David E. Brady and Stephanie Stassel. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Directory Editor's note: All information subject to change. Call ahead 
whenever possible.  
</P>
<P>
 * FEMA Disaster Hot Line 
</P>
<P>
 (800) 525-0321 
</P>
<P>
 (800) 660-8005 TDD 
</P>
<P>
 * FEMA 24-Hour Registration Line 
</P>
<P>
 (800) 462-9029 
</P>
<P>
 (800) 462-7585 TDD 
</P>
<P>
 Registrants can choose to apply for financial assistance over the phone or by 
visiting any FEMA Disaster Aid Center. Be prepared to provide your name, 
address, Social Security number and those of other occupants in the house at 
the time of the quake. Several languages are spoken on both lines. 
</P>
<P>
 * Permit Assistance Center 
</P>
<P>
 (818) 705-7920, 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. weekdays and 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. Saturdays. 
