<P>
 Zenith Chosen by Digital HDTV Alliance: The so-called Digital HDTV grand 
alliance said it selected Zenith Electronics Corp.'s technology as the digital 
transmission subsystem for the high-definition television system it will 
propose to the Federal Communications Commission.The alliance, in cooperation 
with the FCC, last week concluded extensive testing and selected Zenith's VSB 
technology over General Instrument's QAM transmission subsystems. "It's the 
last piece of the puzzle," said Dick Muldoon, a spokesman for American 
Telephone & Telegraph Co., a member of the alliance. The HDTV system is 
scheduled for final verification testing in late 1994 and final field testing 
in early 1995. HDTV aims to provide movie-quality digital images on a flatter, 
larger screen. 
</P>
