<TEXT>
<P>
 Mexico Cuts Natural Gas Imports: As recently as last year, the country looked 
to be facing an ever-rising bill for natural gas imports, but it has slashed 
imports to zero and is even exporting some gas to the United States, officials 
say. Pemex, the state oil and gas monopoly, achieved the reduction partly by 
reducing its own use of natural gas. Down the road, Mexican demand is still 
expected to show strong growth, and Pemex's ability to meet demand depends on 
tapping the country's extensive resources and greatly boosting investment in 
the gas sector, according to officials. 
</P>
