<P>
 Air France Proposes Reorganization: The airline's chairman, Christian Blanc, 
sent a letter to his 40,000 employees proposing a reorganization into a series 
of smaller companies. Blanc, who became chief executive of Air France in 
October, proposed cutting layers of management and decentralizing operations to 
spread responsibility over different geographic zones. The proposal was the 
latest stage in a dialogue Blanc has tried to set up with the carrier's 14 
unions in a search for consensus on savings. 
