<P>
BRIEFCASE: RESTAURANTS/RETAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Greg Johnson / Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Showing Hospitality: Rich Ottaviano, AST Research Corp. senior vice president, 
used UC Irvine's annual executive survey briefing Tuesday to lodge a complaint 
about many civic and business organizations in California.Too many of them call 
businesses only "for a donation, a cocktail party or a golf tournament," he 
said.  
</P>
<P>
 In contrast, out-of-state chambers of commerce actively lobby California 
business executives to move to their locales. "Most states and cities are 
acting like Singapore did five years ago," Ottaviano said. 
</P>
<P>
 That means greeting out-of-town business executives at the airport, scurrying 
to find answers to their questions and generally serving as "a professional 
business organization," Ottaviano said. 
</P>
