<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE LINE: OC HIGH / STUDENT NEWS & VIEWS; SPORTS SHOWDOWNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 High school playoffs for winter sports start this week, and there is no 
shortage of hot contenders: 
</P>
<P>
 * Mater Dei will try for a third consecutive Southern Section boys' basketball 
championship. The Monarchs are ranked second in the nation by USA Today. 
</P>
<P>
 * The unbeaten Brea Olinda girls seek their sixth consecutive section 
basketball title and fourth straight state championship. Also headed into the 
playoffs undefeated is Woodbridge, but the teams aren't on a collision course; 
they compete in different divisions. 
</P>
<P>
 * Marina enters the girls' soccer playoffs ranked No. 1 in the section and 
county. The Vikings shared the Division I title with Claremont last season. In 
boys' soccer, defending Division II champion Santa Ana Valley and Division IV 
co-champions Santa Margarita return as unseeded entrants. The county's 
top-ranked team, Corona del Mar, is seeded fourth in Division IV. 
</P>
<P>
 * Calvary Chapel looks to make it back-to-back section and state wrestling 
titles, and El Modena hopes to improve upon last year's Division I runner-up 
status. 
</P>
</TEXT>
