<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE LINE: OC HIGH / STUDENT NEWS & VIEWS; CULTURES IN SPOTLIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 At Mater Dei High School in Santa Ana, learning about students from other 
cultures is one of the focuses of the Kaleidoscope club, reports the student 
newspaper, the Scarlet Scroll. This month, the club plans guest speakers and 
dances to highlight Black History Month; last month, Asian cultures were 
highlighted and events included food tasting and a dragon dance. 
</P>
<P>
 The club's goal is to bring student attention to many different cultures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
