<P>
 College basketball -- The Associated Press reported erroneously Tuesday that 
Kentucky pulled off the greatest comeback in college basketball history, 
trailing LSU by 31 points before winning, 99-95. The report was based on an 
incorrect entry in the NCAA Record Book. Research by Duke officials showed that 
Tulane led Duke by 32 points before losing a game in 1950. 
